cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper deals with facial expression recognition using deep neural networks and conditional random fields. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed method on publicly available databases indicates the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the focus on facial expressions and their recognition suggests the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
